{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-23T09:37:02.483Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":1},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Managing Python Dependencies with pip and requirements.txt"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Python projects rarely run on the standard library alone. Almost every real-world project pulls in third-party packages — libraries for HTTP requests, data manipulation, machine learning, and more. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"pip"},{"type":"text","text":" is Python's built-in package installer, and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"requirements.txt"},{"type":"text","text":" is the conventional file used to record exactly which packages (and which versions) a project depends on. Together, they form the foundation of Python dependency management, and understanding them well is essential before moving on to more advanced tools like Poetry or Conda."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What pip Is"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"pip"},{"type":"text","text":" stands for "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Pip Installs Packages\""},{"type":"text","text":" (a recursive acronym). It is the standard package manager for Python, included automatically with Python 3.4 and later. Its job is to download packages from the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Python Package Index (PyPI)"},{"type":"text","text":" — a public repository of hundreds of thousands of open-source Python libraries — and install them into your Python environment."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"When you run a command like:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"bash"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"pip install numpy"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"pip reaches out to PyPI, finds the latest version of "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"numpy"},{"type":"text","text":", downloads it, and installs it so your Python code can "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"import"},{"type":"text","text":" it."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"pip can also install packages from:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A specific version on PyPI ("},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"pip install numpy==1.26.0"},{"type":"text","text":")"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A local directory or "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":".whl"},{"type":"text","text":" (wheel) file"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A GitHub repository URL"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"requirements.txt"},{"type":"text","text":" file (covered below)"}]}]}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What requirements.txt Is"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"requirements.txt"},{"type":"text","text":" file is a plain text file that lists all the packages your project needs, one per line. It acts as a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"manifest of dependencies"},{"type":"text","text":" — a snapshot of what needs to be installed for the project to run correctly."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A simple example:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"numpy==1.26.4\npandas==2.2.1\nscikit-learn==1.4.2\nrequests==2.31.0"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Anyone who clones your project can run:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"bash"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"pip install -r requirements.txt"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"...and pip will install every package listed, at the exact versions specified. This makes the project reproducible across different machines, teammates, CI/CD pipelines, and deployment environments."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why It Matters"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Without a way to record and reproduce dependencies, Python projects become fragile. Consider what happens when:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A teammate installs a newer version of a library that breaks your API calls"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A deployment server has a different version of a package than your laptop"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You return to a project six months later and can no longer run it because a dependency updated in a breaking way"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"pip"},{"type":"text","text":" + "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"requirements.txt"},{"type":"text","text":" solves the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"reproducibility problem"},{"type":"text","text":". By pinning exact versions, you ensure that every environment running your project uses the exact same code from every package — eliminating the \"works on my machine\" class of bugs."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"In the context of "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Generative AI projects"},{"type":"text","text":", this is especially critical. Libraries like "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"transformers"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"torch"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"diffusers"},{"type":"text","text":", and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"langchain"},{"type":"text","text":" change rapidly. A version mismatch in "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"torch"},{"type":"text","text":" alone can cause silent numerical differences in model outputs, or outright crashes due to API changes."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"How pip Works — Core Mechanics"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"The PyPI Registry"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"When you run "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"pip install <package>"},{"type":"text","text":", pip queries "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"https://pypi.org"},{"type":"text","text":" (by default) for the package's metadata and available versions. It then downloads the appropriate "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"distribution file"},{"type":"text","text":" — either a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"wheel"},{"type":"text","text":" ("},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":".whl"},{"type":"text","text":", pre-compiled binary) or a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"source distribution"},{"type":"text","text":" ("},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":".tar.gz"},{"type":"text","text":", which needs compilation). Wheels are preferred because they install faster and don't require a C compiler."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Dependency Resolution"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"pip doesn't just install the package you asked for — it also installs all of that package's own dependencies (its "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"transitive dependencies"},{"type":"text","text":"). For example, installing "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"pandas"},{"type":"text","text":" also installs "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"numpy"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"python-dateutil"},{"type":"text","text":", and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"pytz"},{"type":"text","text":" because pandas depends on them."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"As of pip 20.3+, pip uses a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"backtracking dependency resolver"},{"type":"text","text":" that tries to find a set of package versions that satisfies all constraints simultaneously. If it can't, it reports a conflict."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Where Packages Go"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"pip installs packages into the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"site-packages"},{"type":"text","text":" directory of whichever Python interpreter is currently active. This is why virtual environments matter so much — without one, all packages go into the system Python, which creates conflicts between projects. (Virtual environments are covered in the broader series; the key point here is that pip always installs into the currently active environment.)"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Core pip Commands"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Installing Packages"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"bash"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Install the latest version\npip install requests\n\n# Install a specific version\npip install requests==2.31.0\n\n# Install a minimum version\npip install \"requests>=2.28.0\"\n\n# Install a version within a range\npip install \"requests>=2.28.0,<3.0.0\"\n\n# Install from a requirements file\npip install -r requirements.txt\n\n# Install in editable mode (for local development of a package)\npip install -e ."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Inspecting the Environment"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"bash"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# List all installed packages\npip list\n\n# Show details about a specific package (version, location, dependencies)\npip show requests\n\n# Check for outdated packages\npip list --outdated\n\n# Output installed packages in requirements format\npip freeze"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Uninstalling"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"bash"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"pip uninstall requests\n\n# Uninstall everything in a requirements file\npip uninstall -r requirements.txt -y"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Upgrading"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"bash"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Upgrade a package to the latest version\npip install --upgrade requests\n\n# Upgrade pip itself\npip install --upgrade pip"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Working with requirements.txt"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Generating It Automatically"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The most reliable way to generate a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"requirements.txt"},{"type":"text","text":" from your current environment is:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"bash"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"pip freeze > requirements.txt"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"pip freeze"},{"type":"text","text":" outputs every installed package and its exact version in a format suitable for "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"requirements.txt"},{"type":"text","text":". Redirecting it with "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":">"},{"type":"text","text":" writes that output to the file."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Important caveat:"},{"type":"text","text":" If you run "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"pip freeze"},{"type":"text","text":" in a virtual environment, you get only your project's dependencies. If you run it in the system Python, you get everything installed system-wide — which is almost always too much. Always generate "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"requirements.txt"},{"type":"text","text":" from inside a clean virtual environment."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Installing from It"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"bash"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"pip install -r requirements.txt"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"-r"},{"type":"text","text":" flag tells pip to read the file and install everything listed in it."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Format and Syntax"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"requirements.txt"},{"type":"text","text":" supports several syntaxes:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Exact version pin (most reproducible)\nnumpy==1.26.4\n\n# Minimum version (flexible but less reproducible)\nnumpy>=1.24.0\n\n# Compatible release (>=1.24, <2.0)\nnumpy~=1.24.0\n\n# Version range\nnumpy>=1.24.0,<2.0.0\n\n# Install from a GitHub repo (main branch)\ngit+https://github.com/huggingface/transformers.git\n\n# Install from a local path\n./my_local_package\n\n# Include another requirements file\n-r base_requirements.txt\n\n# Specify a package index (e.g., a private registry)\n--index-url https://my.private.registry/simple/\nsome-internal-package==1.0.0"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Splitting Requirements Files"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Large projects often split dependencies into multiple files:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"requirements/\n  base.txt          # Core runtime dependencies\n  dev.txt           # Dev tools: pytest, black, mypy\n  ml.txt            # Heavy ML deps: torch, transformers"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"dev.txt"},{"type":"text","text":" can include "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"base.txt"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"-r base.txt\npytest==8.1.1\nblack==24.3.0\nmypy==1.9.0"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This way:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Production deployments use: "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"pip install -r requirements/base.txt"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Developers use: "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"pip install -r requirements/dev.txt"}]}]}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Version Pinning — The Most Important Concept"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Exact Pinning vs. Flexible Constraints"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"There are two philosophies:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Exact pinning"},{"type":"text","text":" ("},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"=="},{"type":"text","text":"): Every package is locked to a specific version."}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Pro: Perfectly reproducible"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Con: You must manually update versions; you miss security patches"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Flexible constraints"},{"type":"text","text":" ("},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":">="},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"~="},{"type":"text","text":"): You specify a minimum or compatible range."}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Pro: You get updates automatically"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Con: Builds may differ between runs; harder to debug regressions"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Best practice for most projects:"},{"type":"text","text":" Use exact pinning in "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"requirements.txt"},{"type":"text","text":" for reproducibility, but track your "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"intended"},{"type":"text","text":" constraints separately (e.g., in a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"pyproject.toml"},{"type":"text","text":" or comments). Re-generate "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"requirements.txt"},{"type":"text","text":" intentionally when you want to upgrade."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"The Two-File Pattern"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A common pattern is to maintain two files:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"},{"type":"code"}],"text":"requirements.in"},{"type":"text","text":" — human-maintained, high-level constraints:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"torch>=2.0.0\ntransformers>=4.38.0\nfastapi\nuvicorn"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"},{"type":"code"}],"text":"requirements.txt"},{"type":"text","text":" — machine-generated, fully pinned output:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"torch==2.3.0\ntransformers==4.40.0\nfastapi==0.111.0\nuvicorn==0.29.0\n# ... all transitive dependencies pinned too"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The tool "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"pip-compile"},{"type":"text","text":" (from the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"pip-tools"},{"type":"text","text":" package) generates "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"requirements.txt"},{"type":"text","text":" from "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"requirements.in"},{"type":"text","text":" automatically, resolving all transitive dependencies and pinning them. This gives you both human-readable intent and machine-level reproducibility."}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"bash"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"pip install pip-tools\npip-compile requirements.in        # generates requirements.txt\npip-sync requirements.txt          # installs exactly what's in requirements.txt"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Architecture — The Dependency Workflow"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Developer writes code\n        │\n        ▼\nIdentifies needed packages → installs with pip\n        │\n        ▼\n    Virtual Environment\n    (isolated site-packages)\n        │\n        ├── package A v1.2\n        ├── package B v3.0\n        └── package C v2.1 (transitive dep of A)\n        │\n        ▼\npip freeze > requirements.txt\n        │\n        ▼\nrequirements.txt committed to version control (Git)\n        │\n        ▼\nCI/CD or teammate runs:\npip install -r requirements.txt\n        │\n        ▼\nIdentical environment reproduced"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Real-World Example — A Generative AI Project"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Consider a project that fine-tunes a language model using Hugging Face Transformers, exposes it via a FastAPI endpoint, and logs experiments to Weights & Biases."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"},{"type":"code"}],"text":"requirements/base.txt"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":":"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"torch==2.3.0+cu121\ntorchvision==0.18.0+cu121\ntransformers==4.40.0\naccelerate==0.30.0\npeft==0.11.1\ndatasets==2.19.1\nfastapi==0.111.0\nuvicorn[standard]==0.29.0\nwandb==0.16.6"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"},{"type":"code"}],"text":"requirements/dev.txt"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":":"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"-r base.txt\npytest==8.1.1\npytest-asyncio==0.23.6\nhttpx==0.27.0\nblack==24.3.0\nruff==0.4.2\nmypy==1.9.0"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"},{"type":"code"}],"text":".github/workflows/test.yml"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":" (CI):"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"- name: Install dependencies\n  run: pip install -r requirements/dev.txt\n\n- name: Run tests\n  run: pytest tests/"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"On a GPU training machine:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"bash"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"pip install -r requirements/base.txt\npython train.py --model bert-base-uncased --dataset imdb"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This setup ensures:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The training machine, the CI runner, and every developer's laptop all use identical package versions"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The CUDA-specific torch build ("},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"+cu121"},{"type":"text","text":") is explicitly captured"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Dev-only tools don't bloat the production image"}]}]}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Common Mistakes"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Not using a virtual environment."},{"type":"text","text":" Installing with pip into the system Python pollutes the global environment and causes version conflicts between projects. Always activate a virtual environment first."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Committing "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"},{"type":"code"}],"text":"requirements.txt"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":" generated from the system Python."},{"type":"text","text":" This captures unrelated packages and makes the file untrustworthy. Generate it only from a clean project-specific virtual environment."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Never pinning versions."},{"type":"text","text":" Leaving everything as "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"package>=x.y"},{"type":"text","text":" means the environment drifts over time. A deployment six months later may pull in breaking changes."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Over-pinning transitive dependencies manually."},{"type":"text","text":" Don't hand-write pins for packages you didn't directly install. Let "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"pip freeze"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"pip-compile"},{"type":"text","text":" capture transitive dependencies automatically. Hand-maintaining them leads to inconsistencies."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Forgetting to update "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"},{"type":"code"}],"text":"requirements.txt"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":" after installing new packages."},{"type":"text","text":" It's easy to "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"pip install something"},{"type":"text","text":" during development and forget to re-run "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"pip freeze > requirements.txt"},{"type":"text","text":". The next developer or deployment will be missing the package."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Using "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"},{"type":"code"}],"text":"pip freeze"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":" in a dirty environment."},{"type":"text","text":" If you've been experimenting and have leftover packages from other projects or tests, "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"pip freeze"},{"type":"text","text":" captures those too. Start with a fresh virtual environment, install only what the project needs, then freeze."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Not separating dev and production dependencies."},{"type":"text","text":" Installing "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"pytest"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"black"},{"type":"text","text":", and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"mypy"},{"type":"text","text":" into a production Docker image wastes space and increases attack surface. Use split requirements files."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Best Practices"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Always work inside a virtual environment."},{"type":"text","text":" Create one per project with "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"python -m venv.venv"},{"type":"text","text":" and activate it before using pip."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Pin to exact versions for production."},{"type":"text","text":" Use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"=="},{"type":"text","text":" for all packages in production "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"requirements.txt"},{"type":"text","text":". This makes builds reproducible."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"},{"type":"code"}],"text":"pip-tools"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":" for serious projects."},{"type":"text","text":" Maintain human-readable "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"requirements.in"},{"type":"text","text":" and let "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"pip-compile"},{"type":"text","text":" generate the fully pinned "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"requirements.txt"},{"type":"text","text":" with all transitive dependencies resolved."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Commit "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"},{"type":"code"}],"text":"requirements.txt"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":" to version control."},{"type":"text","text":" It should live in the repo so anyone can reproduce the environment. Never "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":".gitignore"},{"type":"text","text":" it."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Review pip's output when installing."},{"type":"text","text":" pip will warn you about conflicts or resolution failures. Don't ignore these warnings."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Audit for security vulnerabilities."},{"type":"text","text":" Use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"pip audit"},{"type":"text","text":" (from the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"pip-audit"},{"type":"text","text":" package) to scan for known CVEs in your dependencies:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"bash"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"pip install pip-audit\npip audit"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Specify CUDA versions for ML projects."},{"type":"text","text":" PyTorch and related libraries have separate builds for different CUDA versions. Pin the exact build tag (e.g., "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"torch==2.3.0+cu121"},{"type":"text","text":") and specify the PyTorch index URL:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"--extra-index-url https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cu121\ntorch==2.3.0+cu121"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Document the Python version too."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"requirements.txt"},{"type":"text","text":" captures packages but not the Python interpreter version. Document the required Python version in "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"README.md"},{"type":"text","text":" or use a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":".python-version"},{"type":"text","text":" file (used by "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"pyenv"},{"type":"text","text":")."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Performance and Scalability Considerations"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Slow installs in CI/CD:"},{"type":"text","text":" pip downloads packages from PyPI on every CI run by default. Speed this up by caching the pip download cache:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# GitHub Actions example\n- uses: actions/cache@v4\n  with:\n    path: ~/.cache/pip\n    key: ${{ runner.os }}-pip-${{ hashFiles('requirements.txt') }}"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Large ML dependencies:"},{"type":"text","text":" Packages like "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"torch"},{"type":"text","text":" can be 2–3 GB. Consider using a pre-built Docker base image that already has torch installed, rather than reinstalling it on every build."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Private packages at scale:"},{"type":"text","text":" For teams with internal packages, set up a private PyPI server (e.g., with "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Artifactory"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"AWS CodeArtifact"},{"type":"text","text":", or "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"devpi"},{"type":"text","text":") and point pip at it using "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"--index-url"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"--extra-index-url"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Parallel installs:"},{"type":"text","text":" pip installs packages sequentially. For very large dependency sets, "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"uv"},{"type":"text","text":" (discussed below) is dramatically faster due to parallel downloading and a Rust-based resolver."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Tooling and Ecosystem"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Tool"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Purpose"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"pip"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Core package installer, built into Python"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"pip-tools"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Generates pinned "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"requirements.txt"},{"type":"text","text":" from high-level "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"requirements.in"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"pip-audit"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Scans installed packages for known security vulnerabilities"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"uv"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Ultra-fast drop-in replacement for pip and pip-tools, written in Rust"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"virtualenv"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Virtual environment creation (predecessor to built-in "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"venv"},{"type":"text","text":")"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"PyPI"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The public package registry pip installs from by default"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Twine"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Uploads packages to PyPI (for package authors)"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"},{"type":"code"}],"text":"uv"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":" deserves special mention."},{"type":"text","text":" Released in 2024 by Astral (the makers of "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"ruff"},{"type":"text","text":"), "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"uv"},{"type":"text","text":" is a modern, extremely fast replacement for pip and pip-tools. It resolves and installs dependencies 10–100x faster than pip, uses the same "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"requirements.txt"},{"type":"text","text":" format, and is becoming widely adopted in production Python toolchains."}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"bash"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Install uv\npip install uv\n\n# Use uv as a drop-in pip replacement\nuv pip install -r requirements.txt\n\n# Generate a locked requirements file (like pip-compile)\nuv pip compile requirements.in -o requirements.txt"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Comparison with Alternatives"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Feature"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"pip + requirements.txt"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"pip-tools"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Poetry"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conda"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"